<ol>
  <li>The 2018 Sutherland Shire Literary Competition is administered by Sutherland Shire Libraries, a service of the Sutherland Shire Council.</li>
  <li>By entering this Competition, you agree to be bound by its Terms and Conditions. To be eligible for any prize or award, you must comply with all of these.</li>
  <h3 class="mt-3">Competition Dates</h3>
  <li>The 2018 Competition opens at 9.00 am (AEDST) on <strong>Monday, 5 February, 2018</strong></li>
  <li>The Competition closes at 11.59 pm (AEST) on <strong>Monday 30 April, 2018.</strong></li>
  <li>Entries will not be accepted after the Competition closes.</li>
  <h3 class="mt-3">Who Can Enter</h3>
  <li>The Competition is open to individuals over 18 years of age who are Australian citizens or permanent residents of Australia and who are living in Australia on the day of entry.</li>
  <li>To be eligible for a special <em>Shire Resident&rsquo;s Prize,</em> an entrant must <em>also</em> be living in the Sutherland Shire Local Government Area (NSW) on the day of entry. (Proof of residence may be required for this Award.)</li>
  <li>Current Councillors and Employees of Sutherland Shire Council, all sponsor organisations and competition judges are ineligible to enter.</li>
  <h3 class="mt-3">Competition Categories and Prizes</h3>
